INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (521, '2012-05-14 15:47:44', 6, 332, '<p>In the sixteenth episode of the first season of Arrested Development, \"Altar E;s,\" we see young Michael Bluth as a lawyer in a play (and again later in the tenth episode of season three, \"Fakin\' It\"):</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p><strong>Narrator:</strong> In order to satisfy an English requirement, Michael appeared\n  in the Drama Club’s production of an original play, “The Trial of\n  Captain Hook.”</p>\n  \n  <p><strong>Young Michael:</strong> (singing) / You’re a  crook, Captain Hook / / Judge, won’t you throw the book at the\n  pirate... /</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/59zTX.jpg\" alt=\"The Trial of Captain Hook\"></p>\n\n<p>Logic suggests they wouldn\'t set up a shot that elaborate for about nine seconds of a joke, but maybe they would. <strong>Is there any additional footage of this play beyond what we see in these two episodes?</strong></p>', 155, 382, NULL, '2012-05-14 21:14:13', 'Is there any additional footage of \'The Trial of Captain Hook,\' the play Michael starred in on Arrested Development?', '<arrested-development>', '2012-06-15 15:47:44');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (522, '2012-05-15 14:09:16', 5, 94, '<p>Towards the end of <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1596365/\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Woman in Black (2012)</a>, Arthur Kipps finds the dead body of the child in the marshes, and he places his dead body into his grave. I thought the grave should have been empty, but there was another corpse (in skeleton form) in that grave. Whose corpse is that?</p>', 1368, 954, '2012-12-12 17:02:53', '2012-12-12 17:02:53', 'Whose corpse is in the grave towards the end of The Woman in Black?', '<plot-explanation><woman-in-black>', '2012-07-05 14:09:16');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (523, '2012-05-15 21:21:04', 9, 320, '<p>For example, <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0209144/\">Memento (2000)</a> is presented as two different sequences of scenes: a series in black-and-white that are shown chronologically, and <strong>a series of color sequences shown in reverse order</strong>. </p>\n\n<p>Another example I can remember is Seinfeld\'s 9th season episode \"The Betrayal\".</p>\n\n<p>Does this style have a name in movie jar;n?</p>', 353, 1034, NULL, '2014-04-02 06:19:13', 'What is the technique called when series of events in a film are played in reverse order?', '<movie-jar;n>', '2012-06-12 21:21:04');
