INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1283, '2013-01-15 16:17:13', 2, 127, '<p>In <em>Blackadder ;es Forth: General Hospital</em> Blackadder reveals that Nurse Mary is the spy.  She is lead away to be shot and then George reveals that he was really giving the information away by sending letters to his uncle.  </p>\n\n<p>Darling and Blackadder then race to the General to tell him.</p>\n\n<p>Why?  </p>\n\n<p>Was she not a spy?  If not then why didn\'t she say so and why did she not spot that Hull was not one of the great universities?  Also, all of the evidence pointed towards her (speaking German, quizzing Blackadder over tank movements etc).</p>\n\n<p>If she was a spy then why rush to tell the General, she would be shot anyway.</p>', 934, 50, '2013-02-17 14:21:36', '2013-02-17 14:21:36', 'Why the rush to get to the general in Blackadder?', '<plot-explanation><blackadder>', '2013-02-08 16:17:13');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1284, '2013-01-16 07:19:10', 10, 21112, '<p>First of all, I have limited knowledge about X Men Comics and that too is from watching the  movies.  </p>\n\n<p>Is there any relation between the character of Victor Creed from <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0458525/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em>X-Men Origins: Wolverine</em></a> and Sabretooth from <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0120903/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em>X-Men</em> (2000)</a>? And if yes, how come he ended up becoming a brainless henchman for Magneto?</p>\n\n<p>IMO, he should have become arch enemy or nemesis of Wolverine. </p>', 816, 1493, '2014-03-29 14:36:34', '2014-03-29 14:36:34', 'Is Victor Creed from \"X-men Origins: Wolverine\" actually Sabretooth?', '<character><x-men><x-men-origins-wolverine>', '2013-02-15 07:19:10');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1285, '2013-01-16 10:42:46', 8, 3967, '<p><strong>A total of 9 directors have been used to direct the Game of Thrones TV series till date.</strong></p>\n\n<p>I was left wondering as to why use so many directors for a single plot story! Wouldn\'t their individual styles and approach to the story contaminate each other? And how would actors react to being directed in a different manner, each episode?!</p>\n\n<p>Is there any reference and justification to the studios decision regarding this? </p>\n\n<p>PS <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0944947/fullcredits\">Here</a> is a list of the directors.</p>', 1358, 834, '2013-01-17 18:22:03', '2014-08-04 13:06:08', 'What is the reason for the many directors used in the Game of Thrones series?', '<directors><game-of-thrones>', '2013-02-07 10:42:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1286, '2013-01-16 11:09:02', 1, 698, '<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/V_The_Serial\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Serial</a> is an Indian soap opera based on the real life of Indian TV Actors. But I want to know how much of the show is real? I mean are there any non celebrity character that is also played by the same person? And how much real is the show?</p>', 954, 1713, '2013-01-16 16:33:11', '2013-01-20 06:47:22', 'How realistic is V The Serial?', '<realism><v-the-serial>', '2013-03-01 11:09:02');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1287, '2013-01-16 13:34:02', 1, 174, '<p>Last year I\'ve watched a trailer which starts like a classic horror movie; youth people ; to a camp in a rural area and all the classic boring things happen. Then they find a building and an elevator in it and things change.</p>\n\n<p>Can anyone recognize this?</p>', 1794, 776, '2013-12-16 14:07:41', '2013-12-16 14:07:41', 'Campers find a building and an elevator', '<identify-this-movie><horror>', '2013-02-11 13:34:02');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1288, '2013-01-16 21:21:00', 6, 597, '<p>In <em>The Dark Knight Rises</em>, Selina Kyle enters the home of John Daggett to confront his henchman for a copy of software she had been promised that would erase her name and criminal record from every database in the world. They deny that the code exists and fight her off. She faces a growing crowd of armed opponents when Batman arrives to help.</p>\n\n<p>How did Batman know she was there? He had placed a tracking device on a necklace she stole near the beginning of the movie, but he had already retrieved the necklace before this scene. Was it coincidence that he arrived at that moment, and if so, why was he visiting Daggett\'s house himself?</p>', 137, 1280, '2013-01-16 22:29:27', '2014-05-24 13:29:56', 'How does Batman know to rescue Selina Kyle outside the home of John Daggett?', '<plot-explanation><dark-knight-rises>', '2013-03-10 21:21:00');
