INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1574, '2013-04-08 05:18:36', 1, 75, '<p>In \"The Hobbit\", the party finds a troll\'s cave with a stash in it. They find a few swords of elvish make, and on the way out Gandolf finds a short sword to give to Bilbo. When he hands it to Bilbo, he tells him, \"it\'s made from elvish steel which means it will glow when orcs and ;blins are near by\". His statement was broad, not specific to the sword that he was giving Bilbo, yet the other swords (the one Gandolf had as well as the ;blin cleaver) did not glow.</p>\n\n<p>What gives?</p>', 1326, 688, NULL, '2013-04-08 05:18:36', 'Why did only Bilbo\'s sword glow?', '<the-hobbit>', '2013-05-04 05:18:36');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1575, '2013-04-08 21:35:59', 3, 2401, '<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Dra;n_Ball_Z_episodes\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dra;n Ball Z</a> was telecasting on Cartoon Network India from many years. Previously it stopped telecasting it in the middle of season 1. Then it disappeared for years and then repeated telecast till the middle of Freza saga and and then same happened till cell saga. And up-to the last run it stops before Kid Buu episode.</p>\n\n<p>So what is the reason of disappearing of the show in Mid-between of season every time? Why didn\'t complete the full run of a season even when its remaining episode are easily available on internet. </p>\n\n<p>Their are some rumors that it\'s because of violent content or promotion of Indian made cartoons. But i am searching for the main reason for it .</p>', 1131, 869, '2013-09-28 19:56:52', '2014-04-15 08:36:58', 'Why do Dra;n Ball Z telecasts always stop mid-season in India?', '<dra;n-ball-z>', '2013-06-05 21:35:59');
