INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1618, '2013-04-22 20:08:46', 7, 1696, '<p>The major plot twist in the 2013 movie <em>Oblivion</em> is virtually identical to the major plot twist in 2009\'s <em>Moon</em>. <em>Oblivion</em> also seems to borrow other details from <em>Moon</em>, such as the phony mission-control and the layout of the scene with the big \"reveal.\"</p>\n\n<p>Is there any formal link between <em>Oblivion</em> and <em>Moon</em>? For example, have the creators of <em>Oblivion</em> in any way indicated that they were inspired by <em>Moon</em>?</p>', 1187, 925, NULL, '2013-07-25 06:25:24', 'Is \"Oblivion\" somehow linked to \"Moon\"?', '<oblivion><moon>', '2013-06-09 20:08:46');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1619, '2013-04-23 03:19:21', -8, 450, '<p>I\'ve heard from several sources that the Total Recall remake is \"humiliatingly bad.\" This may or may not be true, but no matter what, I have no intention of spending close to 3 hours to watch it. I do, however, want to know if the remake retained these 4 special-effects from the original. </p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>The Arnold low-gravity buggy eyeballs</li>\n<li>The 3 tits</li>\n<li>The mini Siamese twin alien</li>\n<li>The full-body disguise.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Were these included in the remake, and how were they presented?</p>', 1468, 721, '2013-05-13 12:27:48', '2013-05-13 12:27:48', '3 scenes from Total Recall: The Original vs. The remake', '<effects><total-recall-2012><remake><total-recall>', '2013-05-22 03:19:21');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1620, '2013-04-23 18:23:48', 2, 3983, '<p>As per Tom Six\'s claim for Human Centipede 2 to make it more graphic and disturbing, making the first film seem like \"My Little Pony compared with part two.\" So why to make it in black and white? </p>\n\n<p>So what is the reason for making it in B&amp;W, is it for censorship issue or for achieving cheap torture porn effect or is it for any other reason?</p>', 476, 1409, '2013-04-24 05:52:18', '2013-04-25 05:54:04', 'What is the reason for making \"Human Centipede 2\" in black and white?', '<directors><black-and-white><human-centipede-2>', '2013-05-14 18:23:48');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1621, '2013-04-23 22:15:50', 3, 89, '<p>Alec Saddler is a boy genius, in fact in the future he ;es on to revolutionise technology with various inventions including \'liquid chip\' technology, amongst other things, that he created both from his own knowledge and that left to him by his father. </p>\n\n<p>He <em>knows</em> that he is clever and takes pleasure in reminding Kiera about it many times throughout the first season. </p>\n\n<p>So, why is it that at the start of the second season he has decided to get a job at an electronics store? Even mediocre programmers can make better money than he\'d earn from selling electronics to consumers so it doesn\'t make sense.</p>', 1199, 318, NULL, '2013-06-24 21:40:54', 'Why is Alec trying to get a job in an Electronics Store?', '<continuum>', '2013-06-13 22:15:50');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1622, '2013-04-24 01:56:23', 4, 3227, '<p>In the final episode of Season 1, Agent Gardiner is introduced and is very suspicious of Kiera, and begins performing a variety of background checks on her.</p>\n\n<p>Just before the major explosion near the end of the episode, he gets a call from \'his superior\' who advises him that a Mr Escher from Section Six has informed his agency to cooperate fully with Kiera.</p>\n\n<p>At the end of the episode, it is clarified that Mr Escher is neither Kellog or Alec. </p>\n\n<p>Who is Mr Escher?</p>', 336, 828, NULL, '2013-07-02 10:06:39', 'Who is Mr Escher?', '<continuum>', '2013-05-25 01:56:23');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1623, '2013-04-24 10:40:25', 7, 536, '<p>In <em>The Dark Knight</em>, when The Joker plans to kill the Mayor at a public gathering. His attempt to shoot the Mayor is foiled by ;rdon. After this we see Joker\'s face in frustration. This is the only time we see Joker without his make up, but the scars on his face are clearly visible.</p>\n\n<p>Why is it that no one noticed this highly unusual man dressed up in a police uniform at this function?</p>', 1147, 1356, '2013-04-24 19:25:08', '2013-04-24 19:25:08', 'Why does no one notice the Joker when he is present as a policeman during the mayor\'s speech?', '<plot-explanation><dark-knight>', '2013-05-14 10:40:25');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1624, '2013-04-24 13:11:16', 7, 789, '<p>In Skyfall movie Bond fights an assassin and captures a casino token in the assassin\'s stuff which he later cashes out. Clearly the token is used as payment for the assassination. Note that assassination fare is likely very high so it\'s a token that yields some really huge sum of money, not a regular casino token that yields several dozen to several hundred USD (or equivalent thereof).</p>\n\n<p>Why is it done this way? What\'s the significance of using a casino token except that it leads Bond to the casino and that lets the plot progress?</p>', 1429, 458, NULL, '2013-05-21 05:02:26', 'Why is a casino token used as payment in Skyfall?', '<plot-explanation><james-bond><skyfall>', '2013-05-26 13:11:16');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1625, '2013-04-24 17:36:51', 3, 448, '<p>In <em>Broken City</em>, there\'s a scene where the character, Jack Valliant, breaks his whiskey glass by squeezing it with his bare hands. I\'d first like to know if this is actually physically possible. Second, I\'d like to know how this might have been done in the movie especially from a safety POV.</p>\n\n<p>Here are a couple of screenshots of the event.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/CDQLK.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/hJvgd.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>I assume that the glass is a prop (that he actually drinks out of) which shatters very easily. However, won\'t it still be a safety hazard? While the actor appears to have mitigated some of the risk by cleverly concealing his face behind his arm, it appears to only be partial. Moreover, the bald guy (commissioner) is unprotected and has shards even falling behind him. These two are clearly not stuntmen either. How would this situation have been handled?</p>', 432, 841, NULL, '2013-04-24 17:40:17', 'Breaking a whiskey glass with your bare hands: how would this have been done?', '<film-techniques><props><stunts><broken-city>', '2013-05-13 17:36:51');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1626, '2013-04-24 21:03:38', 5, 5116, '<p>At the end of the <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1483013/\">film</a>, after <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/character/ch0380361/?ref_=tt_cl_t2\">Beech</a> and <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/character/ch0380358/?ref_=tt_cl_t1\">Tech 49 Jack</a> sacrifice themselves and destroy the ship <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/character/ch0380359/?ref_=tt_cl_t3\">Julia</a> is then seen with a child (who looks about 3 years old). She is then re-introduced to Tech 52 Jack and the way I perceived this was Tech 49 Jacks child but how is this possible if he is dead and there was nothing more than a kiss shown to happen between them?</p>', 566, 675, NULL, '2013-06-12 20:22:07', 'In Oblivion how does Julia get pregnant?', '<plot-explanation><oblivion>', '2013-04-27 21:03:38');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1627, '2013-04-25 12:11:47', 2, 647, '<p>I am a very big fan of  <code>Supernatural</code>. I have watched all seasons of it, but I am confused as to what happened to Lucifer.  The last time we see his is with Sam having hallucinations of Lucifer and then Castile the hallucinations into his mind.</p>\n\n<p>So where is Lucifer now in Supernatural?</p>', 19, 140, '2013-04-25 13:05:54', '2014-08-21 23:26:27', 'Where is Lucifer in Supernatural Season 8?', '<supernatural>', '2013-06-03 12:11:47');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1628, '2013-04-25 14:06:29', 3, 92, '<p>During some scenes it show helicopter and near the end when Old Joe ;es into the mob boss base you see police cars ready to move out. If it\'s organised crime gang why would they help kill Joe?</p>', 646, 1375, NULL, '2013-04-25 14:47:03', 'Why is it that the police are helping track down Joe in Looper (2012)', '<looper>', '2013-05-23 14:06:29');
