INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1630, '2013-04-25 15:48:05', 3, 229, '<p>Presumably, soon after the events of the \"The Doctor\'s Wife,\" the TARDIS gained a holographic interface.  We\'ve seen (\"Let\'s Kill Hitler\") that it can change its appearance.</p>\n\n<p>Why does the TARDIS choose to mirror Clara when it speaks to her in \"Hide\"?</p>', 509, 1201, '2013-12-28 20:02:43', '2013-12-28 20:02:43', 'In the episode \"Hide,\" why does the TARDIS mimic Clara?', '<plot-explanation><doctor-who>', '2013-04-30 15:48:05');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1631, '2013-04-25 21:04:22', 2, 175, '<p>In <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2149175/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em>The Americans</em></a> S01E12 what sort of pin did the KGB-resident give Nina after she swore the oath?  What was it\'s significance and meaning (rank-insignia?  \"shield\"?  medal/order?)?  Was it the KGB-symbol?  It looked like a star with a through/behind...</p>', 497, 735, '2013-04-25 21:28:20', '2013-04-26 03:24:40', 'What is the meaning of pin the KGB-resident gave Nina?', '<plot-explanation><the-americans>', '2013-05-19 21:04:22');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1632, '2013-04-26 08:54:12', 6, 453, '<p>When Hal first reveals to his friend Tom that he is a superhero i.e. The Green Lantern, he is pushed by Tom to show how it works.</p>\n\n<p>Hal puts on the ring and tries to turn into Green Lantern but is unable to do so because apparently, the ring is out of power and thus proceeds to re-charge it with the Lantern.</p>\n\n<p>Now, what happens if Green Lantern\'s ring looses its power/charge/juice when he is mid-flight or in-action? Though this didn\'t happen in the movie but it sounds like a perfectly plausible scenario.</p>\n\n<p><strong>P.S.</strong> <em>I don\'t have any background from the comics universe which might be useful in answering the question.</em></p>', 69, 336, NULL, '2013-05-01 17:34:07', 'What happens when Green Lantern\'s ring runs out of \'juice\'?', '<plot-explanation><green-lantern>', '2013-05-14 08:54:12');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1633, '2013-04-26 14:26:38', 1, 141, '<p>I am looking for a movie I saw about 15 years a; on TV.</p>\n\n<p>There was a <strong>student</strong> who came to a university (I guess) because the university wanted him to play in the <strong>local basketball team</strong>. As a student accepted because of his sport skills, he was not expected to excel in normal subjects so he ;t a personal teacher (a girl from the university) who was supposed to help him with the studies.</p>\n\n<p>I remember that <strong>she gave him a couple of books to read, without any expectation, but when he actually read them she started to change her opinion on him.</strong> The story ;es on and I guess that in the end he quit basketball, as he realized what is really important (knowledge, love, blah blah :D). Even though the movie is quite average, I would like to see it again as I remember that I liked it a lot.</p>\n\n<p>Some additional info (hopefully true):</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>American production.</li>\n<li>From the 90s.</li>\n<li>It is a normal movie, not an animated one.</li>\n</ul>', 674, 1523, '2013-04-26 15:49:28', '2013-04-27 21:04:46', 'A student who plays basketball but likes to read', '<identify-this-movie>', '2013-06-18 14:26:38');
