INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1681, '2013-05-08 13:56:12', 8, 9813, '<p>The kid Harley Keener played a pretty important role in Iron Man 3.  To me it sort of seemed that the movie was hinting that he was ;ing to be another hero, maybe from the Iron Man universe, maybe from the general Marvel universe.</p>\n\n<p>Am I reading too much into this, or is the kid suposed to be important outside just this movie?</p>', 190, 582, '2013-10-17 09:48:13', '2013-11-01 11:04:42', 'Is the kid a reference to another Marvel hero?', '<iron-man-3><marvel-cinematic-universe><marvel>', '2013-06-15 13:56:12');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1682, '2013-05-08 14:04:51', 1, 265, '<p>In several episodes of Doctor Who (The Runaway Bride and the Wedding of River Song spring to mind) the Doctor says that he cannot cross his own timeline for fear of creating a paradox... it\'s obviously a mechanism so the writers can limit him and stop him always \";ing back and fixing things\".</p>\n\n<p>The spoilers below refer to \"The Wedding of River Song\" and the end of the Impossible Astronaut arc</p>\n\n<blockquote class=\"spoiler\">\n  <p> However in The Wedding of River Song river is both on the beach and in the space suit</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>A ;od Man ;es to War Spoiler</p>\n\n<blockquote class=\"spoiler\">\n  <p> In fact Amy\'s actually pregnant with her too so she\'s there a third time!</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Back to tWoRS spoilers</p>\n\n<blockquote class=\"spoiler\">\n  <p> What\'s more the Doctor actually invited her to do it.  Knowing that she was ;ing to kill him he sent the blue envelope so she\'d see her do it?</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>In this case isn\'t River crossing her own timeline?  Why can she do it and the doctor can\'t?</p>', 1799, 1621, NULL, '2013-05-08 20:53:38', 'Wasn\'t River crossing her own timeline?', '<doctor-who>', '2013-06-10 14:04:51');
