INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1684, '2013-05-08 23:31:01', 4, 280, '<p>In the sequence set to the Blue Danube Waltz, we see a Pan Am orbital shuttle docking with a partially-completed space station.  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q3oHmVhviO8\" rel=\"nofollow\">Here</a> is a clip from that sequence on YouTube.  There are ;od views of the space station at 0:02-0:28 and 1:28-1:46 in that clip that keep the camera at a respectful distance, as would be expected given late 1960s technology:  models (since no CGI yet) and large cameras guided on rails (no motion control, either).  But the final shot (1:56-2:17) has the camera viewpoint ; through the structure of the space station!  How was this accomplished?  Was the model the size of a house, or did Kubrick have something else up his sleeve?</p>', 152, 969, '2013-12-05 11:31:44', '2013-12-05 11:31:44', 'How was the space station fly-through in 2001: A Space Odyssey filmed?', '<effects><stanley-kubrick><2001-a-space-odyssey>', '2013-06-06 23:31:01');
