INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1788, '2013-06-03 19:21:02', 10, 394, '<p>Admiral Kirk arrives aboard the Enterprise for an inspection of the training crew. While inspecting the crew as they stand in line. He comes to Scotty and says the following.</p>\n\n<h2>From The Script</h2>\n\n<pre><code>                                       KIRK\n                                 (continuing to Scotty)\n                         Mr. Scott, you old space dog. You\'re\n                         well?\n\n                                       SCOTTY\n                         I had me a wee bout -- but Dr. McCoy\n                         pulled me through.\n\n                                       KIRK\n                         Oh? A wee bout of what, Mr. Scott?\n\n               Uncomfortable, Scotty exchanges a glance with Bones --\n\n                                       BONES\n                         Shore leave, Admiral.\n\n                                       KIRK\n                         Ah.\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/wx3RK.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p>I\'ve have seen this film a number of times, and always wondered. What was wrong with Scotty. It\'s clear that he went to Dr. McCoy for treatment of something, but that it was a personal thing so McCoy says \"Shore leave\" to the Admiral.</p>\n\n<p>I don\'t remember anything happening to Scotty in the first Star Trek film that could be related.</p>', 296, 836, '2013-09-04 11:56:09', '2014-07-31 16:42:19', 'What illness did Scotty have that was treated by Dr. McCoy?', '<star-trek-wrath-of-khan>', '2013-07-28 19:21:02');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1789, '2013-06-04 02:17:15', 6, 413, '<p>I\'ve been trying to figure this one out forever!</p>\n\n<p>I was a child watching this movie and it has bothered me ever since.   I\'ve had this one image from the movie stuck in my head for a long time and I\'m wondering if anyone can identify it.</p>\n\n<p>I watched this movie no later than 1994.  It was an animated movie (or maybe anime?)  </p>\n\n<p>The scene I remember is one where there was a brother and a sister (I think...maybe it was two brothers or two sisters or two friends, but I think it was a brother and a sister).  There are also a lot of other children.  They were in some kind of passage or tunnel or something.  There was a table and food and some one told the brother/older child (?) that he could not eat the food on the table.  The younger (?) ate the food and the two had to be separated.  The one who ate the food had to ; with all the other children who ate the food and the other could ; somewhere else.  I\'m not sure what or where either group was ;ing. </p>\n\n<p>As I was very young when I watched it, it made a big impact on me and I often think of it.  I\'m really curious to see what that movie might have been.</p>', 544, 799, '2013-06-04 10:17:43', '2013-06-04 10:17:43', '80s/early 90s animated movie with a brother and a sister eating forbidden food off a table', '<identify-this-movie><80s><90s>', '2013-07-05 02:17:15');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1790, '2013-06-04 06:03:31', 6, 339, '<p>There were a few things which Andy Dufresne was shown putting into the package which he tied to his foot while escaping. Some of the items were his chess pieces and the account books of the warden. However, during the cell-search the next morning, besides the prison clothes, <strong>a rock hammer and a bar of soap</strong> were discovered to be missing.</p>\n\n<p>The use of account books and rock hammer are apparent but what were the other things that Andy carried and for what purpose?</p>', 72, 962, '2013-06-04 14:58:18', '2013-06-04 18:54:34', 'What other things did Andy Dufresne carry while escaping from Shawshank Prison?', '<shawshank-redemption>', '2013-06-15 06:03:31');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (1791, '2013-06-04 21:40:13', 4, 607, '<p>I\'ve ;t a random memory of a science fiction film from either the late 80s or early 90s. It\'s a fairly sketch memory but a few key points stick out:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Aliens (that look human) travel to earth to stop an human / alien hybrid child</p></li>\n<li><p>They get to earth by teleporting to a roof of a sky scraper (not much in the way of effects, just some smoke and lights!)</p></li>\n<li><p>Parts are more mystical than sci-fi it feels like</p></li>\n<li><p>The hybrid child has telekinetic powers</p></li>\n<li><p>The final battle takes place on the sky scraper and (this is the really clear part I remember) a metal bird statue that is being levitated has a large spike shoot out of it and the statue then is flown into the main bad guy impaling him.</p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>I\'m not sure if this was a movie or something made for TV but it look fairly cheap!</p>', 1068, 1000, '2013-12-28 19:56:49', '2014-09-12 02:33:13', 'Aliens arrive to stop a hybrid child who has telekinetic powers', '<identify-this-movie><identify-this-tv-show><science-fiction><80s><90s>', '2013-07-21 21:40:13');
