INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (2075, '2013-08-11 20:20:47', 4, 279, '<p>Can anybody tell me the name of a movie I saw on TV when I was a kid maybe 20 years a;. My memory of it is a bit hazy but the opening sequence involves a man being hunted by these sadistic assassins through a forest maybe in Alaska or somewhere? The assassins are wearing masks (I think) and one of them uses a bow/crossbow. Anyway, the man is killed. The film seems to be based around a secret military training compound of some sort. A second man, the movie\'s main character, ends up in this compound where he must test his combat skills against the assassins. He fights and kills them all one by one and in the end it turns out he was being set up by the Military group that sent him in there.</p>\n\n<p>Some of the above details maybe be slightly inaccurate as my memory of it is quite faded now. </p>\n\n<p>It\'s not <em>Deadly Prey</em> or <em>Surviving the Game</em>.</p>', 1169, 354, '2013-08-11 20:50:41', '2013-08-11 20:50:41', 'Man being hunted by sadistic assassins through a forest', '<identify-this-movie>', '2013-09-26 20:20:47');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (2076, '2013-08-11 20:25:53', 5, 2459, '<p>In season 4 of Breaking Bad, the relationship between Gus (and subsequently Mike) and the pair of Walt &amp; Jesse is complex.  Gus sets them up with a fully equipped laboratory to cook Meth, but initially Jesse proves unreliable and Walt is forced to defend him from the boss.</p>\n\n<p>As the relationship sours between the parties:</p>\n\n<p>1) Why didn\'t Gus just kill Jesse and leave Walt alone to cook? They could kill Jesse and say to Walt that if you don\'t cook, we will kill your family.</p>\n\n<p>2) Later, why does Gus want to kill Walt and not just fire him and leave him alone?</p>\n\n<p>3) Why did Mike start to take Jesse with him on jobs ?</p>', 575, 516, '2013-08-19 21:25:29', '2013-08-19 23:31:55', 'Relationship between Walt, Jesse and Gus', '<breaking-bad>', '2013-09-12 20:25:53');
