INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (2108, '2013-08-18 08:23:52', 3, 169, '<p>This TV series was broadcast in the 1970s. The story premise was about a young boy who was being kept away from his birth mother who was of some high rank like a princess or other. It was during the emperors and shogun era of Japan. A sad drama type of series.</p>\n\n<p>In the ending song of the episode it says something about his mother that he calls as Hahayue no. I can\'t remember if he was being trained for his higher rank life or becoming a monk. But I think his name was kin-san or something like that. The end song was a very sad soft female voice that sung a letter he wrote to his birth mom and ends with his name.</p>', 835, 503, '2013-08-18 10:24:23', '2013-08-18 13:47:54', '1970s anime about a boy never being able to see his princess mother', '<identify-this-tv-show><anime>', '2013-08-19 08:23:52');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (2109, '2013-08-18 15:46:04', 1, 135, '<p>A movie about a writer who ;es on some kind of strange journey with a talking typewriter. In one scene there are people drinking from straws in people\'s heads, and dealers make an addictive drug from giant centipedes. </p>\n\n<p>The movie came out in the 80\'s or 90\'s.</p>\n\n<p>The movie is on the tip of my tongue but I just can\'t remember what it\'s called.</p>', 1362, 1794, NULL, '2013-08-18 15:54:01', 'A talking typewriter?', '<identify-this-movie>', '2013-10-08 15:46:04');
INSERT INTO `posts` VALUES (2110, '2013-08-18 20:02:36', 2, 155, '<p>In the original, 1974 version of <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0071771/\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Longest Yard</a>, during the big game, the convicts are on the 16 yard line facing fourth and four and Crewe calls for a drop kick.  The kick is successful (though if you watch closely the ball actually ;es far left of the post) so the convicts get 3 points.</p>\n\n<p>My question is: why attempt what was even at the time a pretty obsolete play instead of just kicking a field ;al for the same amount of points?</p>\n\n<p>Earlier in the game Crewe elected to run in an extra point attempt instead of kicking it, but he explained that was because they were showing off and intentionally trying to embarrass the guards.  However, since the drop kick play happened late in the fourth quarter while they were still losing, I would assume Crewe would be much more concerned about winning the game at that point instead of showing off.</p>\n\n<p>Was there a rule in football back then that gave them some advantage to attempting a drop kick?</p>', 1368, 887, '2013-08-18 21:07:04', '2013-08-20 14:58:22', 'In the 1974 version of The Longest Yard, what was the reason for the drop kick?', '<plot-explanation><the-longest-yard>', '2013-09-13 20:02:36');
